text: Gatlukay () is a rural locality (an aul) in Adygeysk District of Adygea, Russia. The population was 1555 as of 2018. There are 15 streets. == Geography == The aul is located 1.5 km east from Adygeysk, 20 km south-east from Krasnodar and 92 km north-east from Maykop. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Circassians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Adygea
title: Gatlukay
